<p><strong>Clifftop neighbourhoods — Top of the World, Arch Beach Heights, Temple Hills (92651).</strong> The elevated residential areas above the city with direct Pacific views and maximum salt air exposure. Homes on Crest Drive, Alta Vista Way, and the Top of the World streets sit at elevation with the ocean breeze hitting every exterior surface year-round. The marine layer here deposits minerals and salt particles on every exposed surface including exterior vent caps and gas connectors. Gas dryer calls from these addresses get our full coastal protocol: flex connector inspection first regardless of stated problem, exterior vent cap damper test, marine-grade dielectric grease on every electrical connection. What we actually find on clifftop Laguna Beach calls: green corrosion buildup on wire harnesses, corroded cap dampers that stick partially closed, gas connectors showing heavy oxidation on machines only 3–4 years old. Last month on Crest Drive — DLGX gas dryer, 4 years old, d80 had been returning every 4–6 weeks after each vent cleaning for two years. The duct was clean. The cap damper was corroded shut — it opened under pressure when the dryer ran but the spring mechanism had corroded enough to stick at 40% closed at rest. Replaced the cap: $35. d80 gone. The persistent d80 pattern is the most specific Laguna Beach clifftop problem — cleaning the duct doesn't fix a cap damper that salt air has corroded shut. We replace rather than clean on clifftop caps.</p>

