<p><strong>Canyon homes — Laguna Canyon, Bluebird Canyon, Mystic Hills (92651, 92653).</strong> The residential neighbourhoods climbing into the canyons east of PCH — homes on Laguna Canyon Road, Bluebird Canyon Drive, Temple Hills Drive, and the side streets feeding off them. More sheltered from direct ocean salt air than the clifftop and beach addresses. Canyon homes in Laguna Beach carry fire risk — the 1993 fires burned through Bluebird Canyon and surrounding areas, and fire awareness runs deep in this community. We have the same vent maintenance as fire prevention conversation in Laguna Canyon homes that we have in Malibu and Pacific Palisades. Canyon debris — dry brush, eucalyptus — enters exterior caps faster than in flat coastal areas. Santa Ana wind events in October and November push debris into caps overnight. We recommend checking exterior cap condition after every significant Santa Ana event in Laguna Canyon and Bluebird Canyon — these are the conditions under which the combination of a partially restricted vent and dry canyon vegetation creates the highest fire risk. Annual vent cleaning plus cap inspection is our standard recommendation for every Laguna Canyon and Bluebird Canyon home.</p>

